  "text": "In this large scale experiment, we follow the methodology used in the extensive pattern matching performance evaluation of [CITATION_1] . We use images from the Pascal VOC 2010 data-set [CITATION_2] , which has been widely used for the evaluation of a variety of computer vision tasks. Each pattern matching instance involves selecting an image at random from the data-set and selecting a random affine transformation, which maps a square template into the image (the mapped square being a random parallelogram). The parallelogram within the image is then warped (by the inverse affine transformation) in order to create the square template. See Fig. 4 for an example.",
